#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:2
msgid "Code of Conduct"
msgstr "Kode Etik"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:5
msgid "Our Pledge"
msgstr "Janji Kami"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:7
msgid "We pledge to make our community welcoming, safe, and equitable for all."
msgstr ""
"Kami berjanji untuk membuat komunitas kami ramah, aman, dan adil bagi semua."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:9
msgid ""
"We are committed to fostering an environment that respects and promotes the "
"dignity, rights, and contributions of all individuals, regardless of "
"characteristics including race, ethnicity, caste, color, age, physical "
"characteristics, neurodiversity, disability, sex or gender, gender identity "
"or expression, sexual orientation, language, philosophy or religion, "
"national or social origin, socio-economic position, level of education, or "
"other status. The same privileges of participation are extended to everyone "
"who participates in good faith and in accordance with this Covenant."
msgstr ""
"Kami berkomitmen untuk menciptakan lingkungan yang menghormati dan "
"menjunjung tinggi martabat, hak, dan kontribusi semua individu, tanpa "
"memandang karakteristik termasuk ras, etnis, kasta, warna kulit, usia, "
"karakteristik fisik, neurodiversitas, disabilitas, jenis kelamin atau "
"gender, identitas atau ekspresi gender, orientasi seksual, bahasa, filsafat "
"atau agama, asal usul kebangsaan atau sosial, status sosial ekonomi, tingkat "
"pendidikan, atau status lainnya. Hak akses partisipasi yang sama diberikan "
"kepada setiap orang yang berpartisipasi dengan itikad baik dan sesuai dengan "
"Kovenan ini."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:12
msgid "Encouraged Behaviors"
msgstr "Perilaku yang Didorong"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:14
msgid ""
"While acknowledging differences in social norms, we all strive to meet our "
"community's expectations for positive behavior. We also understand that our "
"words and actions may be interpreted differently than we intend based on "
"culture, background, or native language."
msgstr ""
"Sembari mengakui perbedaan norma sosial, kami semua berupaya memenuhi "
"harapan komunitas kami akan perilaku positif. Kami juga memahami bahwa "
"perkataan dan tindakan kami dapat ditafsirkan berbeda dari yang kami "
"inginkan berdasarkan budaya, latar belakang, atau bahasa asli."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:16
msgid ""
"With these considerations in mind, we agree to behave mindfully toward each "
"other and act in ways that center our shared values, including:"
msgstr ""
"Dengan mempertimbangkan hal tersebut, kami sepakat untuk berperilaku penuh "
"kesadaran terhadap satu sama lain dan bertindak dengan cara yang berpusat "
"pada nilai bersama kami, termasuk:"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:18
msgid ""
"Respecting the **purpose of our community**, our activities, and our ways of "
"gathering."
msgstr ""
"Menghormati **tujuan komunitas kami**, aktivitas kami, dan cara kami "
"berkumpul."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:19
msgid "Engaging **kindly and honestly** with others."
msgstr "Berinteraksi **dengan baik dan jujur** dengan orang lain."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:20
msgid "Respecting **different viewpoints** and experiences."
msgstr "Menghormati **sudut pandang** dan pengalaman yang berbeda."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:21
msgid "**Taking responsibility** for our actions and contributions."
msgstr "**Mengambil tanggung jawab** atas tindakan dan kontribusi kami."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:22
msgid "Gracefully giving and accepting **constructive feedback**."
msgstr ""
"Memberikan dan menerima **masukan yang mengonstruksikan** dengan anggun."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:23
msgid "Committing to **repairing harm** when it occurs."
msgstr "Berkomitmen untuk **memperbaiki kerusakan** saat terjadi."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:24
msgid ""
"Behaving in other ways that promote and sustain the **well-being of our "
"community**."
msgstr ""
"Berperilaku dengan cara lain yang mempromosikan dan mempertahankan "
"**kesejahteraan komunitas kita**."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:28
msgid "Restricted Behaviors"
msgstr "Perilaku Terbatas"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:30
msgid ""
"We agree to restrict the following behaviors in our community. Instances, "
"threats, and promotion of these behaviors are violations of this Code of "
"Conduct."
msgstr ""
"Kami setuju untuk membatasi perilaku berikut di komunitas kami. Contoh, "
"ancaman, dan promosi perilaku tersebut merupakan pelanggaran Kode Etik ini."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:32
msgid ""
"**Harassment.** Violating explicitly expressed boundaries or engaging in "
"unnecessary personal attention after any clear request to stop."
msgstr ""
"**Pelecehan.** Melanggar batasan yang dinyatakan secara tegas atau terlibat "
"dalam perhatian pribadi yang tidak perlu setelah adanya permintaan yang "
"jelas untuk berhenti."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:33
msgid ""
"**Character attacks.** Making insulting, demeaning, or pejorative comments "
"directed at a community member or group of people."
msgstr ""
"**Serangan karakter.** Membuat komentar yang menghina, merendahkan, atau "
"merendahkan yang ditujukan kepada anggota komunitas atau segrup orang."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:34
msgid ""
"**Stereotyping or discrimination.** Characterizing anyone’s personality or "
"behavior on the basis of immutable identities or traits."
msgstr ""
"**Stereotip atau diskriminasi.** Mengkarakterisasikan kepribadian atau "
"perilaku seseorang berdasarkan identitas atau sifat yang tidak dapat diubah."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:35
msgid ""
"**Sexualization.** Behaving in a way that would generally be considered "
"inappropriately intimate in the context or purpose of the community."
msgstr ""
"**Seksualisasi.** Berperilaku dengan cara yang secara umum dianggap tidak "
"pantas dan intim dalam konteks atau tujuan komunitas."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:36
msgid ""
"**Violating confidentiality**. Sharing or acting on someone's personal or "
"private information without their permission."
msgstr ""
"**Melanggar kerahasiaan**. Membagikan atau memanfaatkan informasi privat "
"atau rahasia seseorang tanpa izin."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:37
msgid ""
"**Endangerment.** Causing, encouraging, or threatening violence or other "
"harm toward any person or group."
msgstr ""
"**Membahayakan.** Menyebabkan, mendorong, atau mengancam kekerasan atau "
"kerugian lain terhadap orang atau grup mana pun."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:38
msgid ""
"Behaving in other ways that **threaten the well-being** of our community."
msgstr ""
"Berperilaku dengan cara lain yang **mengancam kesejahteraan** komunitas kami."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:41
msgid "Other Restrictions"
msgstr "Pembatasan Lainnya"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:43
msgid ""
"**Misleading identity.** Impersonating someone else for any reason, or "
"pretending to be someone else to evade enforcement actions."
msgstr ""
"**Identitas yang menyesatkan.** Meniru identitas orang lain untuk alasan apa "
"pun, atau berpura-pura menjadi orang lain untuk menghindari tindakan "
"penegakan hukum."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:44
msgid ""
"**Failing to credit sources.** Not properly crediting the sources of content "
"you contribute."
msgstr ""
"**Gagal mencantumkan sumber.** Tidak mencantumkan sumber konten yang Anda "
"kontribusikan dengan benar."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:45
msgid ""
"**Promotional materials**. Sharing marketing or other commercial content in "
"a way that is outside the norms of the community."
msgstr ""
"**Materi promosi**. Membagikan konten pemasaran atau komersial lainnya "
"dengan cara yang melanggar norma komunitas."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:46
msgid ""
"**Irresponsible communication.** Failing to responsibly present content "
"which includes, links or describes any other restricted behaviors."
msgstr ""
"**Komunikasi yang tidak bertanggung jawab.** Gagal menyajikan konten yang "
"mencakup, menautkan, atau menggambarkan perilaku terlarang lainnya secara "
"bertanggung jawab."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:50
msgid "Reporting an Issue"
msgstr "Melaporkan Isu"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:52
msgid ""
"Tensions can occur between community members even when they are trying their "
"best to collaborate. Not every conflict represents a code of conduct "
"violation, and this Code of Conduct reinforces encouraged behaviors and "
"norms that can help avoid conflicts and minimize harm."
msgstr ""
"Ketegangan dapat terjadi di antara anggota komunitas, bahkan ketika mereka "
"berusaha sebaik mungkin untuk berkolaborasi. Tidak semua konflik "
"merepresentasikan pelanggaran kode etik, dan Kode Etik ini memperkuat "
"perilaku dan norma yang dianjurkan yang dapat membantu menghindari konflik "
"dan meminimalkan kerugian."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:54
msgid ""
"When an incident does occur, it is important to report it promptly. To "
"report a possible violation, please reach the Community Moderators at "
"community@weblate.org."
msgstr ""
"Ketika suatu insiden terjadi, penting untuk segera melaporkannya. Untuk "
"melaporkan kemungkinan pelanggaran, silakan hubungi Moderator Komunitas di "
"community@weblate.org."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:56
msgid ""
"Community Moderators take reports of violations seriously and will make "
"every effort to respond in a timely manner. They will investigate all "
"reports of code of conduct violations, reviewing messages, logs, and "
"recordings, or interviewing witnesses and other participants. Community "
"Moderators will keep investigation and enforcement actions as transparent as "
"possible while prioritizing safety and confidentiality. In order to honor "
"these values, enforcement actions are carried out in private with the "
"involved parties, but communicating to the whole community may be part of a "
"mutually agreed upon resolution."
msgstr ""
"Moderator Komunitas menanggapi laporan pelanggaran dengan serius dan akan "
"berupaya semaksimal mungkin untuk merespons tepat waktu. Mereka akan "
"menyelidiki semua laporan pelanggaran kode etika, meninjau pesan, log, dan "
"rekaman, atau mewawancarai saksi dan peserta lainnya. Moderator Komunitas "
"akan menjaga investigasi dan tindakan penegakan hukum setransparan mungkin "
"dengan mengutamakan keselamatan dan kerahasiaan. Untuk menghormati nilai "
"ini, tindakan penegakan hukum dilakukan secara privat dengan pihak yang "
"terlibat, tetapi komunikasi dengan seluruh komunitas dapat menjadi bagian "
"dari resolusi yang disepakati bersama."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:60
msgid "Addressing and Repairing Harm"
msgstr "Mengatasi dan Memperbaiki Kerusakan"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:62
msgid ""
"If an investigation by the Community Moderators finds that this Code of "
"Conduct has been violated, the following enforcement ladder may be used to "
"determine how best to repair harm, based on the incident's impact on the "
"individuals involved and the community as a whole. Depending on the severity "
"of a violation, lower rungs on the ladder may be skipped."
msgstr ""
"Jika investigasi oleh Moderator Komunitas menemukan bahwa Kode Etik ini "
"telah dilanggar, jenjang penegakan hukum berikut dapat digunakan untuk "
"menentukan cara terbaik untuk memperbaiki kerugian, berdasarkan dampak "
"insiden terhadap individu yang terlibat dan komunitas secara keseluruhan. "
"Tergantung pada tingkat keparahan pelanggaran, jenjang penegakan hukum yang "
"lebih rendah dapat dilewati."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:64
msgid "Warning"
msgstr "Peringatan"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:66
msgid "Event: A violation involving a single incident or series of incidents."
msgstr ""
"Peristiwa: Pelanggaran yang melibatkan satu insiden atau serangkaian insiden."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:67
msgid "Consequence: A private, written warning from the Community Moderators."
msgstr "Konsekuensi: Peringatan tertulis privat dari Moderator Komunitas."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:68
msgid ""
"Repair: Examples of repair include a private written apology, "
"acknowledgement of responsibility, and seeking clarification on expectations."
msgstr ""
"Perbaikan: Contoh perbaikan meliputi permintaan maaf tertulis secara privat, "
"pengakuan tanggung jawab, dan mencari klarifikasi tentang harapan."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:70
msgid "Temporarily Limited Activities"
msgstr "Aktivitas Terbatas Sementara"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:72
msgid ""
"Event: A repeated incidence of a violation that previously resulted in a "
"warning, or the first incidence of a more serious violation."
msgstr ""
"Peristiwa: Kejadian pelanggaran yang berulang yang sebelumnya mengakibatkan "
"peringatan, atau kejadian pertama pelanggaran yang lebih serius."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:73
msgid ""
"Consequence: A private, written warning with a time-limited cooldown period "
"designed to underscore the seriousness of the situation and give the "
"community members involved time to process the incident. The cooldown period "
"may be limited to particular communication channels or interactions with "
"particular community members."
msgstr ""
"Konsekuensi: Peringatan tertulis privat dengan masa tenang terbatas yang "
"dirancang untuk menekankan keseriusan situasi dan memberi waktu bagi anggota "
"masyarakat yang terlibat untuk memproses insiden tersebut. Masa tenang ini "
"dapat dibatasi pada saluran komunikasi atau interaksi tertentu dengan "
"anggota masyarakat tertentu."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:74
msgid ""
"Repair: Examples of repair may include making an apology, using the cooldown "
"period to reflect on actions and impact, and being thoughtful about re-"
"entering community spaces after the period is over."
msgstr ""
"Perbaikan: Contoh perbaikan dapat mencakup menyampaikan permintaan maaf, "
"menggunakan periode tenang untuk merenungkan tindakan dan dampaknya, dan "
"bersikap bijaksana dalam memasuki kembali ruang komunitas setelah periode "
"tenang berakhir."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:76
msgid "Temporary Suspension"
msgstr "Penghentian Sementara"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:78
msgid ""
"Event: A pattern of repeated violation which the Community Moderators have "
"tried to address with warnings, or a single serious violation."
msgstr ""
"Peristiwa: Pola pelanggaran berulang yang telah coba diatasi oleh Moderator "
"Komunitas dengan peringatan, atau satu pelanggaran serius."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:79
msgid ""
"Consequence: A private written warning with conditions for return from "
"suspension. In general, temporary suspensions give the person being "
"suspended time to reflect upon their behavior and possible corrective "
"actions."
msgstr ""
"Konsekuensi: Peringatan tertulis privat dengan syarat untuk kembali dari "
"skorsing. Umumnya, skorsing sementara memberi waktu kepada orang yang "
"diskors untuk merenungkan perilakunya dan kemungkinan tindakan korektif."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:80
msgid ""
"Repair: Examples of repair include respecting the spirit of the suspension, "
"meeting the specified conditions for return, and being thoughtful about how "
"to reintegrate with the community when the suspension is lifted."
msgstr ""
"Perbaikan: Contoh perbaikan meliputi menghormati semangat penangguhan, "
"memenuhi persyaratan yang ditentukan untuk pengembalian, dan bersikap "
"bijaksana tentang cara berintegrasi kembali dengan masyarakat saat "
"penangguhan dicabut."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:82
msgid "Permanent Ban"
msgstr "Larangan Permanen"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:84
msgid ""
"Event: A pattern of repeated code of conduct violations that other steps on "
"the ladder have failed to resolve, or a violation so serious that the "
"Community Moderators determine there is no way to keep the community safe "
"with this person as a member."
msgstr ""
"Peristiwa: Pola pelanggaran kode etik yang berulang yang gagal diatasi pada "
"jenjang yang lain, atau pelanggaran yang begitu serius sehingga Moderator "
"Komunitas memutuskan tidak ada cara untuk menjaga keamanan komunitas dengan "
"orang ini sebagai anggota."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:85
msgid ""
"Consequence: Access to all community spaces, tools, and communication "
"channels is removed. In general, permanent bans should be rarely used, "
"should have strong reasoning behind them, and should only be resorted to if "
"working through other remedies has failed to change the behavior."
msgstr ""
"Konsekuensi: Akses ke semua ruang komunitas, perangkat, dan saluran "
"komunikasi dihapuskan. Secara umum, larangan permanen sebaiknya jarang "
"digunakan, harus memiliki alasan yang kuat, dan hanya boleh dilakukan jika "
"upaya lain tidak berhasil mengubah perilaku."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:86
msgid "Repair: There is no possible repair in cases of this severity."
msgstr "Perbaikan: Tidak ada kemungkinan perbaikan dalam kasus seserius ini."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:88
msgid ""
"This enforcement ladder is intended as a guideline. It does not limit the "
"ability of Community Managers to use their discretion and judgment, in "
"keeping with the best interests of our community."
msgstr ""
"Tangga penegakan hukum ini dimaksudkan sebagai pedoman. Tangga ini tidak "
"membatasi kemampuan Pengelola Komunitas untuk menggunakan kebijaksanaan dan "
"penilaian mereka, demi kepentingan terbaik komunitas kita."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:94
msgid ""
"This Code of Conduct applies within all community spaces, and also applies "
"when an individual is officially representing the community in public or "
"other spaces. Examples of representing our community include using an "
"official email address, posting via an official social media account, or "
"acting as an appointed representative at an online or offline event."
msgstr ""
"Kode Etika ini berlaku di semua ruang komunitas, dan juga berlaku ketika "
"seseorang secara resmi merepresentsikan komunitas di ruang publik atau ruang "
"lainnya. Contoh merepresentsikan komunitas kami antara lain menggunakan "
"alamat surel resmi, memposting melalui akun media sosial resmi, atau "
"bertindak sebagai representatif yang ditunjuk di acara daring maupun luring."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:98
msgid "Attribution"
msgstr "Atribusi"

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:100
msgid ""
"This Code of Conduct is adapted from the Contributor Covenant, version 3.0, "
"permanently available at https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/3/0/."
msgstr ""
"Kode Etik ini diadaptasi dari Perjanjian Kontributor, versi 3.0, tersedia "
"secara permanen di https://www.contributor-covenant.org/version/3/0/."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:102
msgid ""
"Contributor Covenant is stewarded by the Organization for Ethical Source and "
"licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0. To view a copy of this license, visit https://"
"creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/."
msgstr ""
"Contributor Covenant dikelola oleh Organization for Ethical Source dan "
"dilisensikan di bawah CC BY-SA 4.0. Untuk melihat salinan lisensi ini, "
"kunjungi https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/."

#: contributing/code_of_conduct.rst:104
msgid ""
"For answers to common questions about Contributor Covenant, see the FAQ at "
"https://www.contributor-covenant.org/faq. Translations are provided at "
"https://www.contributor-covenant.org/translations. Additional enforcement "
"and community guideline resources can be found at https://www.contributor-"
"covenant.org/resources. The enforcement ladder was inspired by the work of "
"`Mozilla’s code of conduct team <https://github.com/mozilla/inclusion>`_."
msgstr ""
"Untuk jawaban atas pertanyaan umum tentang Kovenan Kontributor, silakan "
"lihat FAQ di https://www.contributor-covenant.org/faq. Terjemahan tersedia "
"di https://www.contributor-covenant.org/translations. Sumber daya penegakan "
"hukum dan pedoman komunitas lainnya dapat ditemukan di https://"
"www.contributor-covenant.org/resources. Tangga penegakan hukum ini "
"terinspirasi oleh karya `tim kode etik Mozilla <https://github.com/mozilla/"
"inclusion>`_."

#: contributing/communication.rst:2
msgid "Weblate Contributor Communication Guidelines"
msgstr "Pedoman Komunikasi Kontributor Weblate"

#: contributing/communication.rst:5
msgid "GitHub Issues"
msgstr "Isu GitHub"

#: contributing/communication.rst:6
msgid ""
"`GitHub Issues <https://github.com/WeblateOrg/weblate/issues>`_ is where "
"bugs can be reported, and features can be requested. Issue submission form "
"provides templates for each to simplify issue creation, and review and "
"implementation process; it also guides to other places with information like "
"documentation, Discussions, HackerOne program, and Weblate Care."
msgstr ""
"`Isu GitHub <https://github.com/WeblateOrg/weblate/issues>`_ adalah tempat "
"kesalahan dapat dilaporkan, dan fitur dapat diminta. Formulir pengiriman isu "
"menyediakan templat untuk setiap masalah guna menyederhanakan pembuatan "
"masalah, serta proses peninjauan dan implementasi; formulir ini juga memandu "
"ke tempat lain dengan informasi seperti dokumentasi, Diskusi, program "
"HackerOne, dan Weblate Care."

#: contributing/communication.rst:11
msgid "Weblate GitHub Discussions"
msgstr "Diskusi Weblate GitHub"

#: contributing/communication.rst:12
msgid ""
"`GitHub Discussions <https://github.com/WeblateOrg/weblate/discussions>`_ is "
"a community place. Ideas, Polls, Q&A, and Show and Tell categories can be "
"selected when posting there. General category fits all posts outside those "
"defined categories. Weblate team members occasionally visit Discussions and "
"can also be mentioned by their GitHub usernames."
msgstr ""
"`Diskusi GitHub <https://github.com/WeblateOrg/weblate/discussions>`_ adalah "
"wadah komunitas. Kategori Ide, Polling, Tanya Jawab, dan Tampilkan dan "
"Ceritakan dapat dipilih saat memposting di sana. Kategori umum cocok untuk "
"semua postingan di luar kategori yang telah ditentukan. Anggota tim Weblate "
"terkadang mengunjungi Diskusi dan juga dapat disebutkan dengan nama pengguna "
"GitHub mereka."

#: contributing/communication.rst:18
msgid "Weblate on Mastodon"
msgstr "Weblate di Mastodon"

#: contributing/communication.rst:19
msgid ""
"If you want to attract a wide community of Weblate users, fans, and "
"developers to your case, you can follow and mention `@weblate@fosstodon.org "
"<https://fosstodon.org/@weblate>`_ on Mastodon. The Weblate team boosts good "
"moods and bright ideas!"
msgstr ""
"Jika Anda ingin menarik komunitas pengguna, penggemar, dan pengembang "
"Weblate yang luas untuk bergabung dengan komunitas Anda, Anda dapat "
"mengikuti dan menyebutkan `@weblate@fosstodon.org <https://fosstodon.org/"
"@weblate>`_ di Mastodon. Tim Weblate akan meningkatkan suasana hati dan ide "
"cemerlang!"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:2
msgid "Debugging Weblate"
msgstr "Mengawakutu Weblate"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:4
msgid ""
"Bugs can behave as application crashes or as various misbehavior. You are "
"welcome to collect info on any such issue and submit it to the `issue "
"tracker <https://github.com/WeblateOrg/weblate/issues>`_."
msgstr ""
"Kerusakan dapat berupa mogok aplikasi atau berbagai perilaku buruk. Anda "
"dipersilakan untuk mengumpulkan informasi tentang isu tersebut dan "
"mengirimkannya ke `pelacak isu <https://github.com/WeblateOrg/weblate/"
"issues>`_."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:9
msgid "Debug mode"
msgstr "Mode awakutu"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:11
msgid ""
"Turning on debug mode will make the exceptions show in the web browser. This "
"is useful to debug issues in the web interface, but not suitable for a "
"production environment because it has performance consequences and might "
"leak private data."
msgstr ""
"Mengaktifkan mode awakutu akan menampilkan pengecualian di peramban web. Ini "
"berguna untuk mengawakutu masalah di antarmuka web, tetapi tidak cocok untuk "
"lingkungan produksi karena dapat memengaruhi kinerja dan berpotensi "
"membocorkan data privat."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:15
msgid ""
"In a production environment, use :setting:`ADMINS` to receive e-mails "
"containing error reports, or configure error collection using a third-party "
"service."
msgstr ""
"Dalam lingkungan produksi, gunakan :setting:`ADMINS` untuk menerima surel "
"yang berisi laporan galat, atau konfigurasikan pengumpulan galat menggunakan "
"layanan pihak ketiga."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:27
msgid "Weblate logs"
msgstr "Catatan Weblate"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:29
msgid ""
"Weblate can produce detailed logs of what is going on in the background. In "
"the default configuration it uses syslog and that makes the log appear "
"either in :file:`/var/log/messages` or :file:`/var/log/syslog` (depending on "
"your syslog daemon configuration)."
msgstr ""
"Weblate dapat menghasilkan catatan rinci tentang apa yang terjadi di latar "
"belakang. Dalam konfigurasi bawaan, Weblate menggunakan syslog, sehingga "
"catatan muncul di :file:`/var/log/messages` atau :file:`/var/log/syslog` "
"(tergantung konfigurasi daemon syslog Anda)."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:34
msgid ""
"The Celery process (see :ref:`celery`) usually produces its own logs as "
"well. The example system-wide setups logs to several files under :file:`/var/"
"log/celery/`."
msgstr ""
"Proses Celery (lihat :ref:`celery`) biasanya juga menghasilkan catatannya "
"sendiri. Contoh pengaturan catatan di seluruh sistem disimpan dalam beberapa "
"berkas di bawah :file:`/var/log/celery/`."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:37
msgid ""
"Docker containers log to their output (as per usual in the Docker world), so "
"you can look at the logs using ``docker compose logs``. You can get more "
"detailed logs by changing :envvar:`WEBLATE_LOGLEVEL`."
msgstr ""
"Kontainer Docker mencatat keluarannya (seperti biasa di dunia Docker), jadi "
"Anda bisa melihat catatan tersebut menggunakan ``docker compose logs``. Anda "
"bisa mendapatkan catatan yang lebih rinci dengan "
"mengubah :envvar:`WEBLATE_LOGLEVEL`."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:43
msgid ""
":ref:`sample-configuration` contains :setting:`django:LOGGING` configuration."
msgstr ""
":ref:`sample-configuration` berisi konfigurasi :setting:`django:LOGGING`."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:48
msgid "Not processing background tasks"
msgstr "Tidak memproses tugas latar belakang"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:50
msgid ""
"A lot of things are done in the background by Celery workers. If things like "
"sending out e-mails or component removal does not work, there might a "
"related issue."
msgstr ""
"Banyak hal yang dilakukan di latar belakang oleh pekerja Celery. Jika hal-"
"hal seperti mengirim surel atau penghapusan komponen terjadi kegagalan, "
"mungkin ada masalah yang saling terkait."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:54
msgid "Things to check in that case:"
msgstr "Hal yang harus diperiksa dalam kasus itu:"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:56
msgid "Check that the Celery process is running, see :ref:`celery`"
msgstr "Periksa apakah proses Celery sedang berjalan, lihat :ref:`celery`"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:57
msgid ""
"Check the Celery queue status, either in :ref:`management-interface`, or "
"using :wladmin:`celery_queues`"
msgstr ""
"Periksa status antrian Celery, baik di :ref:`management-interface`, atau "
"menggunakan :wladmin:`celery_queues`"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:58
msgid "Look in the Celery logs for errors (see :ref:`weblate-logs`)"
msgstr "Lihat catatan Celery untuk galat (lihat :ref:`weblate-logs`)"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:63
msgid "Not receiving e-mails from Weblate"
msgstr "Tidak menerima surel dari Weblate"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:65
msgid ""
"You can verify whether outgoing e-mail is working correctly by using "
"the :djadmin:`django:sendtestemail` management command (see :ref:`invoke-"
"manage` for instructions on how to invoke it in different environments) or "
"by using :ref:`management-interface` under the :guilabel:`Tools` tab."
msgstr ""
"Anda dapat memverifikasi apakah surel keluar berfungsi dengan benar dengan "
"menggunakan perintah pengelolaan :djadmin:`django:sendtestemail` "
"(lihat :ref:`invoke-manage` untuk petunjuk tentang cara memanggilnya di "
"lingkungan yang berbeda) atau dengan menggunakan :ref:`management-interface` "
"di bawah tab :guilabel:`Alat`."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:70
msgid ""
"These send e-mails directly, so this verifies that your SMTP configuration "
"is correct (see :ref:`out-mail`). Most of the e-mails from Weblate are "
"however sent in the background and there might be some issues with Celery "
"involved as well, please see :ref:`debug-tasks` for debugging that."
msgstr ""
"Surel ini dikirim secara langsung, sehingga memverifikasikan bahwa "
"konfigurasi SMTP Anda sudah benar (lihat :ref:`out-mail`). Namun, sebagian "
"besar surel dari Weblate dikirim di latar belakang dan mungkin ada beberapa "
"isu dengan Celery juga. Silakan lihat :ref:`debug-tasks` untuk "
"mengawakutunya."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:76
msgid "Analyzing application crashes"
msgstr "Menganalisis mogok aplikasi"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:78
msgid ""
"In case the application crashes, it is useful to collect as much info about "
"the crash as possible. This can be achieved by using third-party services "
"which can collect such info automatically. You can find info on how to set "
"this up in :ref:`collecting-errors`."
msgstr ""
"Jika aplikasi mengalami mogok, ada baiknya mengumpulkan informasi sebanyak "
"mungkin tentang mogok tersebut. Hal ini dapat dilakukan dengan menggunakan "
"layanan pihak ketiga yang dapat mengumpulkan informasi tersebut secara "
"otomatis. Anda dapat menemukan informasi tentang cara mengaturnya "
"di :ref:`collecting-errors`."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:84
msgid "Silent failures"
msgstr "Kegagalan yang senyap"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:86
msgid ""
"Lots of tasks are offloaded to Celery for background processing. Failures "
"are not shown in the user interface, but appear in the Celery logs. "
"Configuring :ref:`collecting-errors` helps you to notice such failures "
"easier."
msgstr ""
"Banyak tugas yang dialihkan ke Celery untuk diproses di latar belakang. "
"Kegagalan tidak ditampilkan di antarmuka pengguna, tetapi muncul di catatan "
"Celery. Mengkonfigurasikan :ref:`collecting-errors` akan membantu Anda "
"mendeteksi kegagalan tersebut dengan lebih mudah."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:91
msgid "Performance issues"
msgstr "Isu kinerja"

#: contributing/debugging.rst:93
msgid ""
"In case Weblate performs badly in some scenario, please collect the relevant "
"logs showing the issue, and anything that might help figuring out where the "
"code might be improved."
msgstr ""
"Jika Weblate tidak berfungsi dengan baik dalam skenario tertentu, silakan "
"kumpulkan catatan relevan yang menunjukkan isu tersebut, dan apa pun yang "
"dapat membantu menentukan bagian kode yang dapat diperbaiki."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:97
msgid ""
"See :ref:`collecting-errors` for information on setting up Sentry which can "
"provide useful insights on badly performing operations."
msgstr ""
"Lihat :ref:`collecting-errors` untuk informasi tentang pengaturan Sentry "
"yang dapat memberikan wawasan berguna tentang operasi yang berkinerja buruk."

#: contributing/debugging.rst:100
msgid ""
"In case the slow performance is linked to the database, you can also enable "
"logging of all database queries using following configuration after "
"enabling :setting:`DEBUG`:"
msgstr ""
"Jika kinerja lambat terkait dengan basis data, Anda juga dapat mengaktifkan "
"pencatatan semua kueri basis data menggunakan konfigurasi berikut setelah "
"mengaktifkan :setting:`DEBUG`:"

#: contributing/documentation.rst:2
msgid "Contribute to Weblate documentation"
msgstr "Kontribusikan pada dokumentasi Weblate"

#: contributing/documentation.rst:4
msgid ""
"You are welcome to improve the documentation page of your choice. Do it "
"easily by clicking the :guilabel:`Edit on GitHub` button in the top-right "
"corner of the page."
msgstr ""
"Silakan sempurnakan halaman dokumentasi pilihan Anda. Anda dapat "
"melakukannya dengan mudah dengan mengeklik tombol :guilabel:`Sunting di "
"GitHub` di pojok kanan atas halaman."

#: contributing/documentation.rst:8
msgid "Documentation guidelines"
msgstr "Pedoman dokumentasi"

#: contributing/documentation.rst:10
msgid "Please respect these guidelines while writing:"
msgstr "Harap hormati pedoman berikut saat menulis:"

#: contributing/documentation.rst:12
msgid "Don’t remove part of the documentation if it’s valid."
msgstr "Jangan hapus bagian dari dokumentasi jika valid."

#: contributing/documentation.rst:13
msgid ""
"Use clear and easily-understandable language. You are writing tech docs, not "
"a poem. Not all docs readers are native speakers, be thoughtful."
msgstr ""
"Gunakan bahasa yang jelas dan mudah dipahami. Anda sedang menulis dokumen "
"teknis, bukan puisi. Tidak semua pembaca dokumen adalah penutur asli, jadi "
"berhati-hatilah."

#: contributing/documentation.rst:15
msgid ""
"Don’t be afraid to ask if you are not certain. If you have to ask about some "
"feature while editing, don’t change its docs before you have the answer. "
"This means: You change or ask. Don’t do both at the same time."
msgstr ""
"Jangan ragu untuk bertanya jika Anda tidak yakin. Jika Anda perlu bertanya "
"tentang suatu fitur saat menyunting, jangan ubah dokumennya sebelum Anda "
"mendapatkan jawabannya. Artinya: Anda mengubah atau bertanya. Jangan lakukan "
"keduanya secara bersamaan."

#: contributing/documentation.rst:18
msgid ""
"Verify your changes by performing described actions while following the docs."
msgstr ""
"Verifikasikan perubahan Anda dengan melakukan tindakan yang dijelaskan saat "
"mengikuti dokumen."

#: contributing/documentation.rst:19
msgid ""
"Send PR with changes in small chunks to make it easier and quicker to review "
"and merge."
msgstr ""
"Kirim PR dengan perubahan dalam potongan kecil agar lebih mudah dan cepat "
"dalam meninjau dan menggabungkan."

#: contributing/documentation.rst:20
msgid ""
"If you want to rewrite and change the structure of a big article, do it in "
"two steps:"
msgstr ""
"Jika Anda ingin menulis ulang dan mengubah struktur artikel besar, lakukan "
"dalam dua langkah:"

#: contributing/documentation.rst:22
msgid "Rewrite"
msgstr "Tulis kembali"

#: contributing/documentation.rst:23
msgid ""
"Once the rewrite is reviewed, polished, and merged, change the structure of "
"the paragraphs in another PR."
msgstr ""
"Setelah tulisan ulang ditinjau, dipoles, dan digabungkan, ubah struktur "
"paragraf dalam PR lain."

#: contributing/documentation.rst:26
msgid "Building the documentation locally"
msgstr "Membangun dokumentasi secara lokal"

#: contributing/documentation.rst:28
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Documentation can be also edited and built locally, the Python "
#| "requirements are in the ``docs`` dependency group "
#| "in :file:`pyproject.toml`. The build can be performed using :program:`ci/"
#| "run-docs`."
msgid ""
"Documentation can be also edited and built locally, the Python requirements "
"are in the ``docs`` dependency group in :file:`pyproject.toml`. If you "
"already use the full development environment, ``uv sync --all-extras --dev`` "
"is enough. For documentation work only, ``uv sync --group docs`` is "
"sufficient."
msgstr ""
"Dokumentasi juga dapat disunting dan dibangun secara lokal. Persyaratan "
"Python terdapat dalam grup dependensi ``docs`` di :file:`pyproject.toml`. "
"Pembangunan dapat dilakukan menggunakan :program:`ci/run-docs`."

#: contributing/documentation.rst:33
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "The recommended Weblate configuration verifies:"
msgid "The recommended local workflow is:"
msgstr "Konfigurasi Weblate yang direkomendasikan memverifikasi:"

#: contributing/documentation.rst:40
msgid ""
"The :program:`ci/run-docs` wrapper builds the documentation with warnings "
"treated as errors."
msgstr ""

#: contributing/documentation.rst:45
msgid ""
"You will also need :program:`graphviz` installed to build the documentation."
msgstr ""
