#: workflows.rst:47
msgid ""
"The :ref:`access control <access-control>` is not discussed in detail as a "
"whole in the workflows, as most of its options can be applied to any "
"workflow. Please consult the respective documentation on how to manage "
"access to translations."
msgstr ""
":ref:`Kontrol akses <access-control>` tidak dibahas secara bawaan secara "
"keseluruhan dalam alur kerja, karena sebagian besar opsinya dapat diterapkan "
"ke alur kerja apa pun. Silakan lihat dokumentasi terkait tentang cara "
"mengelola akses ke terjemahan."

#: workflows.rst:52
msgid ""
"In the following chapters, *any user* means a user who has access to the "
"translation. It can be any authenticated user if the project is public, or a "
"user with :guilabel:`Translate` permission to the project."
msgstr ""
"Dalam bab selanjutnya, *setiap pengguna* berarti pengguna yang memiliki "
"akses ke terjemahan. Ini bisa berupa pengguna terautentikasikan apa pun jika "
"proyek bersifat publik, atau pengguna dengan izin :guilabel:`Terjemahkan` ke "
"proyek tersebut."

#: workflows.rst:61
msgid "Each translated string can be in one of the following states:"
msgstr ""
"Setiap string yang diterjemahkan dapat berada dalam salah satu status "
"berikut:"

#: workflows.rst:63
msgid "Untranslated"
msgstr "Belum diterjemahkan"

#: workflows.rst:64
msgid ""
"Translation is empty, it might or not be stored in the file, depending on "
"the file format."
msgstr ""
"Terjemahan kosong, mungkin disimpan dalam berkas atau tidak, tergantung pada "
"format berkas."

#: workflows.rst:67
msgid ""
"Translation needs editing, this is usually the result of fuzzy matching or "
"translator action. Depending on the file format it might be marked as "
"needing edit (for example as it gets a ``fuzzy`` flag in the gettext file)."
msgstr ""
"Terjemahan perlu disunting, ini secara umumnya hasil dari pencocokan fuzzy "
"atau tindakan penerjemah. Tergantung pada format berkas itu mungkin ditandai "
"sebagai perlu disunting (misalnya karena itu mendapatkan penanda ``fuzzy`` "
"dalam berkas gettext)."

#: workflows.rst:69
msgid "Needs rewriting"
msgstr "Perlu ditulis ulang"

#: workflows.rst:70
msgid "Translation needs to be rewritten because of a source string change."
msgstr ""

#: workflows.rst:71
msgid "Needs checking"
msgstr "Perlu diperiksa"

#: workflows.rst:72
msgid ""
"State used for source/template strings that need developer review. It is "
"typically set for new source strings imported from the VCS when the Source "
"edit addon is enabled, or when a source string is reported for checking."
msgstr ""

#: workflows.rst:76
msgid "Translated / Waiting for review"
msgstr "Diterjemahkan / Menunggu untuk ditinjau"

#: workflows.rst:77
msgid ""
"Translation is made. The translated state is shown as \"Waiting for review\" "
"if reviews are enabled."
msgstr ""

#: workflows.rst:79
msgid ""
"Translation has been approved in the review. It can no longer be changed by "
"translators, but only by reviewers. Translators can only add suggestions to "
"it."
msgstr ""
"Terjemahan telah disetujui dalam proses peninjauan. Terjemahan tidak dapat "
"diubah lagi oleh penerjemah, tetapi hanya oleh peninjau. Penerjemah hanya "
"dapat menambahkan saran."

#: workflows.rst:83
msgid "This state is only available when reviews are enabled."
msgstr "Status ini hanya tersedia saat tinjauan diaktifkan."

#: workflows.rst:84
msgid "Read-only"
msgstr "Hanya baca"

#: workflows.rst:85
msgid ""
"String is read-only as a result of having ``read-only`` :ref:`flag <custom-"
"checks>`, being a non-editable source string, or marked such in the "
"translation file."
msgstr ""
"String bersifat hanya baca karena memiliki ``read-only`` :ref:`penanda "
"<custom-checks>`, menjadi string sumber yang tidak dapat disunting, atau "
"ditandai demikian dalam berkas terjemahan."

#: workflows.rst:89
msgid "Suggestions are stored in Weblate only and not in the translation file."
msgstr "Saran hanya disimpan di Weblate dan tidak dalam berkas terjemahan."

#: workflows.rst:91
msgid "The states are represented in the translation files when possible."
msgstr "Status direpresentasikan dalam berkas terjemahan jika memungkinkan."

#: workflows.rst:95
msgid ""
"If the file format you use does not support storing states, you might want "
"to use the :ref:`addon-weblate.flags.same_edit` add-on to flag unchanged "
"strings as needing rewriting."
msgstr ""
"Jika format berkas yang Anda gunakan tidak mendukung status penyimpanan, "
"Anda mungkin ingin menggunakan pengaya :ref:`addon-weblate.flags.same_edit` "
"untuk menandai string yang belum diubah sebagai perlu menulis ulang."

#: workflows.rst:101
msgid ""
"The :ref:`project-commit_policy` determines which translation states are "
"stored in the file."
msgstr ""
":ref:`project-commit_policy` menentukan mana status terjemahan disimpan di "
"berkas."

#: workflows.rst:110
msgid "Direct translation"
msgstr "Terjemah langsung"

#: workflows.rst:111
msgid ""
"The most common setup for smaller teams, where anybody can translate "
"directly. This is also the default setup in Weblate."
msgstr ""
"Pengaturan paling umum untuk tim yang lebih kecil, di mana siapa pun dapat "
"menerjemahkan secara langsung. Ini juga merupakan pengaturan bawaan di "
"Weblate."

#: workflows.rst:114
msgid "*Any user* can edit translations."
msgstr "*Setiap pengguna* dapat menyunting terjemahan."

#: workflows.rst:115
msgid ""
"Suggestions are optional ways to suggest changes, when translators are not "
"sure about the change."
msgstr ""
"Saran adalah cara opsional untuk menyarankan perubahan, ketika penerjemah "
"tidak yakin tentang perubahan tersebut."

#: workflows.rst:119 workflows.rst:151 workflows.rst:184
msgid "Setting"
msgstr "Pengaturan"

#: workflows.rst:119 workflows.rst:151 workflows.rst:184
msgid "Note"
msgstr "Catatan"

#: workflows.rst:121 workflows.rst:126 workflows.rst:153 workflows.rst:191
msgid "off"
msgstr "mati"

#: workflows.rst:121 workflows.rst:153 workflows.rst:186
msgid "Configured at project level."
msgstr "Dikonfigurasikan pada tingkat proyek."

#: workflows.rst:123 workflows.rst:155 workflows.rst:157 workflows.rst:186
#: workflows.rst:188
msgid "on"
msgstr "nyala"

#: workflows.rst:123 workflows.rst:188
msgid "Useful for users to be able to suggest when they are not sure."
msgstr ""
"Berguna bagi pengguna untuk dapat memberi saran ketika mereka tidak yakin."

#: workflows.rst:130 workflows.rst:162 workflows.rst:195
msgid "Translators group"
msgstr "Grup penerjemah"

#: workflows.rst:130 workflows.rst:162 workflows.rst:195
msgid "Or `Translate` with :ref:`per-project access control <manage-acl>`."
msgstr ""
"Atau `Terjemahkan` dengan :ref:`kontrol akses per-proyek <manage-acl>`."

#: workflows.rst:134 workflows.rst:166 workflows.rst:199
msgid "Reviewers group"
msgstr "Grup peninjau"

#: workflows.rst:134 workflows.rst:166
msgid "N/A"
msgstr "Tidak Ada"

#: workflows.rst:134
msgid "Not used."
msgstr "Tidak digunakan."

#: workflows.rst:141
msgid "Peer review"
msgstr "Tinjauan sejawat"

#: workflows.rst:143
msgid ""
"With this workflow, anybody can add a suggestion, which needs approval from "
"additional members before it is accepted as a translation."
msgstr ""
"Dengan alur kerja ini, siapa pun dapat menambahkan saran, yang memerlukan "
"persetujuan dari anggota tambahan sebelum diterima sebagai terjemahan."

#: workflows.rst:146
msgid "*Any user* can add suggestions."
msgstr "*Setiap pengguna* dapat menambahkan saran."

#: workflows.rst:147
msgid "*Any user* can vote for suggestions."
msgstr "*Pengguna mana pun* dapat memberikan suara untuk saran."

#: workflows.rst:148
msgid ""
"Suggestions become translations when given a predetermined number of votes."
msgstr "Saran menjadi terjemahan ditentukan oleh jumlah suara."

#: workflows.rst:159
msgid "You can set higher value to require more peer reviews."
msgstr ""
"Anda dapat mengatur nilai yang lebih tinggi untuk memerlukan lebih banyak "
"tinjauan sejawat."

#: workflows.rst:166
msgid "Not used, all translators review."
msgstr "Tidak digunakan, semua penerjemah meninjau."

#: workflows.rst:172
msgid "Dedicated reviewers"
msgstr "Peninjau khusus"

#: workflows.rst:174
msgid ""
"With dedicated reviewers you have two groups of users, one able to submit "
"translations, and one able to review them to ensure translations are "
"consistent and that the quality is good."
msgstr ""
"Dengan peninjau khusus, Anda memiliki dua grup pengguna, satu dapat "
"mengirimkan terjemahan, dan satu dapat meninjaunya untuk memastikan "
"terjemahan konsisten dan kualitasnya bagus."

#: workflows.rst:178
msgid "*Any user* can edit unapproved translations."
msgstr "*Setiap pengguna* dapat menyunting terjemahan yang tidak disetujui."

#: workflows.rst:179
msgid "*Reviewer* can approve / unapprove strings."
msgstr "*Peninjau* dapat menyetujui/tidak menyetujui string."

#: workflows.rst:180
msgid "*Reviewer* can edit all translations (including approved ones)."
msgstr ""
"*Peninjau* dapat menyunting semua terjemahan (termasuk yang disetujui)."

#: workflows.rst:181
msgid "Suggestions can also be used to suggest changes for approved strings."
msgstr ""
"Saran juga dapat digunakan untuk menyarankan perubahan untuk string yang "
"disetujui."

#: workflows.rst:199
msgid "Or `Review` with :ref:`per-project access control <manage-acl>`."
msgstr "Atau `Tinjau` dengan :ref:`kontrol akses per-proyek <manage-acl>`."

#: workflows.rst:205
msgid "Turning on reviews"
msgstr "Mengaktifkan tinjauan"

#: workflows.rst:207
msgid ""
"Reviews can be turned on in the project configuration, from "
"the :guilabel:`Workflow` subpage of project settings (to be found in "
"the :guilabel:`Operations` → :guilabel:`Settings` menu):"
msgstr ""
"Tinjauan dapat dinyalakan dalam konfigurasi proyek, dari "
"subhalaman :guilabel:`Alur Kerja` pada pengaturan proyek (dapat ditemukan "
"dalam menu :guilabel:`Operasi` → :guilabel:`Pengaturan`):"

#: workflows.rst:214
#, fuzzy
#| msgid "Per language"
msgid "Per-language reviews"
msgstr "Per bahasa"

#: workflows.rst:216
msgid ""
"To require review only for selected languages, first turn on :ref:`project-"
"translation_review` for the whole project. Then open each project language "
"page that should use different behavior, enable :guilabel:`Customize "
"translation workflow for this language in this project`, and "
"turn :guilabel:`Enable reviews` off for languages that should not require "
"review."
msgstr ""

#: workflows.rst:223
msgid ""
"Reviewers also need review access for the same language. Add them to a team "
"whose roles include :guilabel:`Review strings`, and limit that team or the "
"user membership to the language they should review. See :ref:`manage-acl` "
"and :ref:`custom-acl` for language-scoped access setup."
msgstr ""

#: workflows.rst:228
msgid ""
"If approval buttons are not visible, check both parts of the setup: reviews "
"have to be enabled for that translation, and the signed-in user has to have "
"review permission for that language."
msgstr ""

#: workflows.rst:235
msgid "Quality gateway for the source strings"
msgstr "Gerbang kualitas untuk string sumber"

#: workflows.rst:237
msgid ""
"The original source language strings usually come from developers, since "
"they write the code and provide the initial strings. However, developers are "
"often not native speakers of the source language and do not provide the "
"desired quality of the source strings. The intermediate translation can help "
"you address this - there is an additional quality gateway for the strings "
"between developers and translators."
msgstr ""
"String bahasa sumber asli biasanya berasal dari pengembang, karena merekalah "
"yang menulis kode dan menyediakan string awal. Namun, pengembang seringkali "
"bukan penutur asli bahasa sumber dan tidak memberikan kualitas string sumber "
"yang diinginkan. Terjemahan perantara dapat membantu Anda mengatasi hal ini "
"- terdapat gerbang kualitas tambahan untuk string antara pengembang dan "
"penerjemah."

#: workflows.rst:244
msgid ""
"By setting the :ref:`component-intermediate`, this file is used for "
"translating strings to the source language by translators/editors while it "
"is owned by the developers (often using arbitrary languages such as "
"``en_devel``). Once this stage is done, strings are available for "
"translations to target languages, based on what is now a polished source "
"language stored in the :ref:`component-template`."
msgstr ""
"Dengan mangatur :ref:`component-intermediate`, berkas ini digunakan untuk "
"menerjemahkan string ke bahasa sumber oleh penerjemah/penyunting, sementara "
"berkas tersebut dimiliki oleh pengembang (seringkali menggunakan bahasa yang "
"sembarangan seperti ``en_devel``). Setelah tahap ini selesai, string "
"tersedia untuk diterjemahkan ke bahasa target, berdasarkan bahasa sumber "
"yang telah disempurnakan yang tersimpan di :ref:`component-template`."

#: workflows.rst:297
msgid "String consolidation using secondary language"
msgstr "Konsolidasi string menggunakan bahasa kedua"

#: workflows.rst:299
msgid ""
"When :ref:`component-intermediate` cannot be used to consolidate the "
"strings, you can choose one of the translations to act as a secondary "
"language. The language can be configured in a project (:ref:`project-"
"secondary_language`) or in a component (:ref:`component-"
"secondary_language`). It is then shown to the translators while translating "
"(see :ref:`secondary-languages`) and can be optionally used as a source for "
"machine translations (see :ref:`mt-sources`)."
msgstr ""
"Jika :ref:`component-intermediate` tidak dapat digunakan untuk menggabungkan "
"string, Anda dapat memilih salah satu terjemahan untuk bertindak sebagai "
"bahasa kedua. Bahasa tersebut dapat dikonfigurasikan dalam proyek "
"(:ref:`project-secondary_language`) atau dalam komponen (:ref:`component-"
"secondary_language`). Bahasa tersebut kemudian ditampilkan kepada penerjemah "
"saat menerjemahkan (lihat :ref:`secondary-languages`) dan dapat secara "
"opsional digunakan sebagai sumber untuk terjemahan mesin (lihat :ref:`mt-"
"sources`)."

#: workflows.rst:307
msgid ""
"This setup can be useful with mixed language source strings and "
"consolidating them into a single translation, which is then used as a "
"baseline for other work."
msgstr ""
"Pengaturan ini dapat berguna dengan rangkaian sumber bahasa campuran dan "
"menggabungkannya menjadi satu terjemahan, yang kemudian digunakan sebagai "
"dasar untuk pekerjaan lain."

#: workflows.rst:313
msgid "Source strings reviews"
msgstr "Tinjauan string sumber"

#: workflows.rst:315
msgid ""
"With :ref:`project-source_review` enabled, the review process can be applied "
"for source strings. Once enabled, users can report issues with source "
"strings. The actual process depends on whether bilingual or monolingual "
"formats are in use."
msgstr ""
"Dengan :ref:`project-source_review` diaktifkan, proses peninjauan dapat "
"diterapkan untuk string sumber. Setelah diaktifkan, pengguna dapat "
"melaporkan isu dengan string sumber. Proses sebenarnya bergantung pada "
"apakah format dwibahasa atau ekabahasa yang digunakan."

#: workflows.rst:319
msgid ""
"For monolingual formats, source string review functions similarly "
"to :ref:`reviews` — once an issue with a source string is reported, the "
"source string is marked as :guilabel:`Needs editing`."
msgstr ""
"Untuk format ekabahasa, fungsi peninjauan string sumber mirip "
"dengan :ref:`reviews` — setelah isu dengan string sumber dilaporkan, string "
"sumber ditandai sebagai :guilabel:`Perlu disunting`."

#: workflows.rst:323
msgid ""
"Bilingual formats do not allow direct editing of source strings (these are "
"typically extracted directly from the source code). In this case, "
"a :guilabel:`Source needs review` label is attached to strings reported by "
"translators. You should review such strings and either edit them in the "
"source code, or remove the label."
msgstr ""
"Format dwibahasa tidak memungkinkan penyuntingan langsung string sumber "
"(string ini biasanya diekstrak langsung dari kode sumber). Dalam hal ini, "
"label :guilabel:`Sumber perlu ditinjau` dilampirkan pada string yang "
"dilaporkan oleh penerjemah. Anda harus meninjau string tersebut dan "
"menyuntingnya di kode sumber, atau menghapus label tersebut."

